## The Argument

FUTON0 is the cyborg interface layer ‚Äî the membrane where human vitality becomes
stack-legible and stack state becomes human-perceivable. The Stack HUD is the
primary implementation: it reads vitality signals from existing traces (commit
times, recording cadence, Tatami sessions) and presents stack state (boundaries,
liveness, patterns, reminders) in a glanceable frame ‚Äî zero extra lifelogging.
Voice-to-text, text-to-speech (podcast synthesis uses both), Kinesis board, and
the HUD demonstrate that human‚Üístack and stack‚Üíhuman channels work. The
infrastructure substrate ‚Äî Alacritty, Emacs, Linode, FUTON1, Org, pattern sync,
Codex, Claude ‚Äî provides the plumbing. Health and alignment monitoring will
infer actual health from traces (commit times ‚Üí sleep, activity ‚Üí energy) plus
role alignment. Affect signals will track moments of insight and emotional
valence through logged agent sessions, sitting between futon0 and futon3.
Epistemic rhythm will establish weekly/monthly review cycles that bound WIP.
Consulting reuse will systematize proto-pattern extraction. Stack stewardship
will formalize daily practices. Futonic co-evolution will make symbolic signals
of future environments legible through Compass, with literary work entering at
that stage. Together these ground the stack's perception ‚Äî the done prototypes
prove the interface works; the planned prototypes make it health-aware,
affect-sensitive, and generative.


